 <table-wrap-foot class="table-wrap-foot">
  <fn id="TFN1" class="fn">
   <p id="P65" class="p">
    <italic class="italic">Note</italic>. FD and CD anomalies (units of micrograms per cubic meter) are averaged over the Southwest domain; SPEI02 anomalies (unitless) are averaged over different domains within 25–41°N and 117–98°W for each season (see 
    <xref rid="F1" ref-type="fig" class="xref">Figures 1</xref> and 
    <xref rid="F2" ref-type="fig" class="xref">2</xref>). The 95% confidence interval (CI) of the slope value is calculated by bootstrap resampling. CD = coarse dust; FD = fine dust; DJF = December–February; MAM = March–May; JJA = June–August; SON = September–November; SPEI = Standardized Precipitation-Evapotranspiration Index.
   </p>
  </fn>
